article.description: — Marcus Burk had 25 points and six assists as IUPUI defeated Green Bay 80-71 on Friday.
article.headline: Burk leads IUPUI over Green Bay 80-71
article.linkText: Burk leads IUPUI over Green Bay 80-71
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- — Marcus Burk had 25 points and six assists as IUPUI defeated Green Bay 80-71 on Friday. Jaylen Minnett added 21 points and Elyjah Goss had 15 points and 11 rebounds for IUPUI (5-7, 4-7 Horizon League). Mike DePersia added six assists. Burk hit 11 of 13 free throws. IUPUI scored 49 second-half points, a season high. Amari Davis had 26 points for the Phoenix (5-14, 5-10). Emmanuel Ansong added 15 points and seven rebounds.
